<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[189,303,1578,1604]" box="[189,303,1578,1604]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,1578,1604]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,1578,1604]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[189,1399,1626,2027]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Although the subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alcock" authorityYear="1898" box="[471,588,1626,1652]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Actaeinae">Actaeinae</taxonomicName>
has been well studied by many authors, one name that was missed by most revisors is 
<taxonomicName authority="Klunzinger, 1913" authorityName="Klunzinger" authorityYear="1913" box="[371,711,1664,1690]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Actaeodius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[371,501,1664,1690]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Actaeodius</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Klunzinger C. B." box="[506,711,1664,1690]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="97 - 402" refId="ref6869" refString="Klunzinger C. B. 1913. Die Rundkrabben (Cyclometopa) des Roten Meeres. Nova Acta Abhandlungen der Kaiserlich Leop. - Carol. Deutschen Akademie der Naturforscher 99 (2): 97 - 402. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 13073" type="journal article" year="1913">Klunzinger, 1913</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. For instance, the name is not listed in the revisionary studies and compilations by 
<bibRefCitation author="Serene R." box="[432,596,1701,1727]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" refId="ref7392" refString="Serene R. 1984. Crustaces Decapodes Brachyoures de l'Ocean Indien occidental et de la Mer Rouge. Xanthoidea: Xanthidae et Trapeziidae. Addendum: Crosnier A. Carpiliidae et Menippidae. Faune Tropicale 24, Editions de l'ORSTOM, Paris." type="journal volume" year="1984">Serène (1984)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Ng P. K. L. &amp; Guinot D. &amp; Davie P. J. F." box="[651,840,1701,1728]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="1 - 286" refId="ref7096" refString="Ng P. K. L., Guinot D. &amp; Davie P. J. F. 2008. Systema Brachyurorum: Part I. An annotated checklist of extant brachyuran crabs of the world. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology supplement 17: 1 - 286." type="journal article" year="2008">
Ng 
<emphasis box="[693,751,1701,1727]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Klunzinger C. B." box="[850,1124,1701,1727]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="97 - 402" refId="ref6869" refString="Klunzinger C. B. 1913. Die Rundkrabben (Cyclometopa) des Roten Meeres. Nova Acta Abhandlungen der Kaiserlich Leop. - Carol. Deutschen Akademie der Naturforscher 99 (2): 97 - 402. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 13073" type="journal article" year="1913">Klunzinger (1913: 231)</bibRefCitation>
established 
<taxonomicName authority="Klunzinger, 1913" authorityName="Klunzinger" authorityYear="1913" box="[1268,1398,1701,1727]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Actaeodius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1268,1398,1701,1727]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Actaeodius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Klunzinger" authorityYear="1913" box="[244,361,1739,1765]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Actaodius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[244,361,1739,1765]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Actäodius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”) when discussing the taxonomy of 
<taxonomicName authority="(White, 1848)" baseAuthorityName="White" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[795,1162,1739,1765]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Actaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fragifera">
<emphasis box="[795,989,1739,1765]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Actaea fragifera</emphasis>
(White, 1848)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Heller, 1861)" baseAuthorityName="Heller" baseAuthorityYear="1861" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Actaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polyacantha">
<emphasis box="[1220,1398,1739,1765]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">A. polyacantha</emphasis>
(Heller, 1861)
</taxonomicName>
. He decided that these names were synonyms and described and illustrated the species as “ 
<taxonomicName box="[202,415,1813,1840]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Actaodius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fragifer">
<emphasis box="[202,415,1813,1840]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Actäodius fragifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”. 
<bibRefCitation author="Guinot D." box="[441,722,1813,1840]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" refId="ref6661" refString="Guinot D. 1976. Constitution de quelques groupes naturels chez les Crustaces Decapodes Brachyoures. I. La superfamille des Bellioidea et trois sous-familles de Xanthidae (Polydectinae Dana, Trichiinae de Haan, Actaeinae Alcock). Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, Serie A 97, Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, Paris." type="journal volume" year="1976">Guinot (1976: 236–237)</bibRefCitation>
followed and treated Klunzinger’s “ 
<taxonomicName box="[1143,1356,1813,1840]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Actaodius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fragifer">
<emphasis box="[1143,1356,1813,1840]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Actäodius fragifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Heller" baseAuthorityYear="1861" box="[357,591,1851,1877]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Actaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polyacantha">
<emphasis box="[357,591,1851,1877]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Actaea polyacantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The status of the genus, however, has not been discussed. Although 
<bibRefCitation author="Klunzinger C. B." box="[189,407,1888,1914]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="97 - 402" refId="ref6869" refString="Klunzinger C. B. 1913. Die Rundkrabben (Cyclometopa) des Roten Meeres. Nova Acta Abhandlungen der Kaiserlich Leop. - Carol. Deutschen Akademie der Naturforscher 99 (2): 97 - 402. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 13073" type="journal article" year="1913">Klunzinger (1913)</bibRefCitation>
did not specifically state which was the 
<typeStatus box="[878,929,1889,1915]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Klunzinger, 1913" authorityName="Klunzinger" authorityYear="1913" box="[1059,1189,1888,1914]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Actaeodius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1059,1189,1888,1914]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Actaeodius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, his synonymy of the two treated species means that 
<taxonomicName authority="White, 1848" authorityName="White" authorityYear="1848" box="[602,984,1926,1952]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Chlorodius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fragifer">
<emphasis box="[602,831,1926,1952]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Chlorodius fragifer</emphasis>
White, 1848
</taxonomicName>
is the 
<typeStatus box="[1064,1115,1926,1952]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus by monotypy. Currently, the two species are regarded as distinct species of 
<emphasis box="[1028,1177,1964,1990]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Haan" authorityYear="1833" box="[1028,1109,1964,1990]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Actaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">Actaea</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1116,1177,1964,1989]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Odhner T." box="[1237,1394,1963,1990]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="1 - 92" refId="ref7145" refString="Odhner T. 1925. Monographierte Gattungen der Krabbenfamilie Xanthidae. I. Goteborgs Kungliga Vetenskaps-och Vitterhets-Samhalles Handlingar, serie 4 29 (1): 1 - 92." type="journal article" year="1925">Odhner 1925</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Guinot D." box="[189,340,2001,2027]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" refId="ref6661" refString="Guinot D. 1976. Constitution de quelques groupes naturels chez les Crustaces Decapodes Brachyoures. I. La superfamille des Bellioidea et trois sous-familles de Xanthidae (Polydectinae Dana, Trichiinae de Haan, Actaeinae Alcock). Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, Serie A 97, Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, Paris." type="journal volume" year="1976">Guinot 1976</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ng P. K. L. &amp; Guinot D. &amp; Davie P. J. F." box="[352,525,2001,2027]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="1 - 286" refId="ref7096" refString="Ng P. K. L., Guinot D. &amp; Davie P. J. F. 2008. Systema Brachyurorum: Part I. An annotated checklist of extant brachyuran crabs of the world. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology supplement 17: 1 - 286." type="journal article" year="2008">
Ng 
<emphasis box="[395,454,2001,2027]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
